`apps/user-manager-web` is a React + Vite app using SuperTokens for auth. Package manager: **pnpm** (Node workspace). Dev server on port `3000` per Vite config, calling the API at `:3001`.

Source layout (`src/`):

- `main.tsx` — entrypoint (`createRoot`, `StrictMode`).
- `App.tsx` — root component; initializes SuperTokens, sets up `react-router-dom` routes, wraps app in `SuperTokensWrapper` / `ComponentWrapper`.
- `config.tsx` — SuperTokens frontend config (varies by auth recipe).
- `Home/index.tsx` — public landing page (`/`).
- `Dashboard/index.tsx` — protected route (`/dashboard`, guarded by `SessionAuth`).

Routes: `/` (public), `/auth` (SuperTokens pre-built UI), `/dashboard` (protected).

Commands: `nx serve user-manager-web`, `nx build user-manager-web`, `nx lint user-manager-web`. Vite config in `vite.config.ts`.
